Good. The old `ThemeProxy` in the old version of `components/overlay.ts` was:
```ts
export type ThemeProxy = {
	fg: (variant: string, text: string) => string;
	bg: (variant: string, text: string) => string;
};
```

The new version is:
```ts
import type { Theme } from "@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent";
export type ThemeProxy = Pick<Theme, "fg" | "bg">;
```

This is more precise because it picks the exact overload signatures from the Theme class. Nothing constructs a ThemeProxy manually - it's always used as a type for a Theme instance.

